reviewText: The title is misleading. The characters are not related other than they think they are (well almost all) This has a thin science fiction plot with lots of animated sex. Vol. 1 has no tentacles or torture or anything too strange. (The characters want sex.) There are 2 disks (chapters) each with 3 short 'episodes' for the amount of total play time (1 hour, 40 mins.) it could have been burned to one disk. There is NO regional coding. It is subtitled only. No mosaics. Definitely an adult CD with lots of sex, not much plot but what there is serves as a reason for more sex.
Cheap, sells on sex, dumb characters, not funn, corny. Machsit! Belittles women

Didn't think I would enjoy it as much as I did. A light-hearted, guilty pleasure, and when it ended, I honestly didn't want it to end!  I could see this as a television series, there's so much that could be mined from the characters & what's happened so far...

As sex farces go, this is as good as it gets. It reflects it's time faithfully. I refrains from moralizing, does not demonize anyone and maintains a light touch. It is superficial, but appropriately so. A voyeuristic lighthearted entertainment. I am surprised that I had not heard of it before.
Our current politics and mindset would view this as sexist and decadent. Ahhhh, for the good old days.
